  "notes": [
    "Version 3: expanded alias table from 23 to ~110 x86-64 opcodes.",
    "Bucket costs validated against Agner Fog throughput tables: integer ALU baseline, memory ~2x, FP/vector ~2.8x, call ~3x.",
    "Loop-depth frequency weighting (10^depth) now active; weighted energy > raw energy for loop-body code.",
    "The pass emits structured function, block, and line scopes so downstream consumers can evolve without changing the LLVM output format.",
    "Alias coverage should be expanded from real opcode traces collected from representative workloads."
  ]
